sleepworker has been sucessfully tested on ubuntu >= 10.04 with x86 and x86_64. Please drop us a short mail, if it runs sucessfully on hardware or operatingsystems other than that.

What libraries are required? You'll need only the standard C libraries. It is common, that these libraries are shipped as distribution packages for an easy installation.

The installation process is fairly simple:

  $ cd sleepworker/
  $ ./configure
  $ make
  # make install

The uninstallation process is analogous:

  $ cd sleepworker/
  # make uninstall

